  P_5 (m=2):
    Aut(P_p) = AGL(1,5) = Z_5 ⋊ Z_2
    |Aut| = 10
    p ≡ 1 (mod 4)
    -1 in QR? True (expected: True)
    p ≡ 1 mod 4: AGL contains x -> -x (orientation-preserving)
    Irreps of AGL(1,5):
      2 one-dimensional (from Z_m quotient)
      2 representations of dimension 2 (from QR and NQR orbits)
      Check: 2*1^2 + 2*2^2 = 10 = p*m = 10

  P_7 (m=3):
    Aut(P_p) = AGL(1,7) = Z_7 ⋊ Z_3
    |Aut| = 21
    p ≡ 3 (mod 4)
    -1 in QR? False (expected: False)
    p ≡ 3 mod 4: AGL is CHIRAL (no orientation-reversing automorphism)
    Tournament is self-complementary via x -> -x (NOT an automorphism)
    Irreps of AGL(1,7):
      3 one-dimensional (from Z_m quotient)
      2 representations of dimension 3 (from QR and NQR orbits)
      Check: 3*1^2 + 2*3^2 = 21 = p*m = 21

