======================================================================
DIHEDRAL SYMMETRY BREAKING: EVEN vs ODD n
======================================================================
  n odd: Regular tournaments exist, full dihedral symmetry D_m preserves score (m,...,m)
  n even: No regular tournament, best is 'almost regular' (m,m,...,m+1,m+1,...)
          Dihedral symmetry broken: D_m -> S_{n/2} × S_{n/2}
  This explains WHY the H landscape has spurious maxima at even n:
  The symmetry-breaking from D_m to S_{n/2}² creates 'frustration'
  in the spin glass, manifesting as local optima in the flip graph.

  CONJECTURE (HYP-741): At odd n, the H landscape has no spurious
  local maxima. At even n, spurious maxima exist with H = f(n)
  determined by the degree-4 Fourier energy barrier.


